    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Objects resulting from the process of transferring emulsion from a dye diffusion transfer print onto a secondary support. This support is most often paper but may be any other surface that the emulsion will adhere to.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052950/Carr, Polaroid Manipulations (2002)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052949/Grey, Photographer's Guide to Polaroid Transfer (2001)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Het aanbrengen van de emulsie van een kleurenafdruk die is gemaakt met een overdrachtsprinter op een ander materiaal waar de emulsie aan blijft plakken, gewoonlijk papier.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>將感光乳劑自染料擴散轉移沖洗照轉移到複製品的支托面後所產生的物件。此製程最常用的支托面是紙張，但也可能為任何感光乳劑所能附著的表面。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
